Project Findings — Walmart Weekly Sales Forecasting
ISA 444 Final Project · 20 top-volume Store/Department series · 4-week horizon · 5-fold non-overlapping CV

Overview
This project forecast weekly sales for the top 20 Store/Department combinations from the Walmart Kaggle dataset and compared 9 forecasting models spanning four categories: classical baselines, statistical models, gradient-boosted trees, deep neural networks, and a zero-shot foundation model. Models that support exogenous regressors were given access to holiday flags, markdown promotions, store characteristics, and temperature; the rest were run univariate.
Every model used the same 5-fold non-overlapping cross-validation setup at a 4-week horizon, so all metrics are directly comparable.

